transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra, how can I assist you?

Speaker 2: Hi, yes, I'm calling to cancel a prescription.

Speaker 1: Sure.

Speaker 2: Can I have your name as well as your date of birth?

Speaker 1: Yep, Paul Musso, December 15, 1956.

Speaker 2: Okay, while I'm pulling up your account, Mr. Musso,

Speaker 1: may I ask the reason for wanting to cancel?

Speaker 2: Because the VA is providing it to me right now,

Speaker 1: so I don't need to buy it anymore.

Speaker 2: Okay, so I see that you are currently getting our Viagra,

Speaker 1: and you said you're getting it from the VA.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: Okay, now we do have our Viagra AGB,

Speaker 2: which is a different Viagra than what you were getting.

Speaker 1: Did you want to maybe try that out and see how that works for you?

Speaker 2: No, that's what I originally had tried to order,

Speaker 1: but they sent me just the regular kind,

Speaker 2: and they kept sending it every month.

Speaker 1: I had originally wanted to try that,

Speaker 2: but now I don't want to try it anymore.

Speaker 1: Okay, understood, no problem.

Speaker 2: I'm going to go ahead and cancel this for you, okay?

Speaker 1: Okay, thank you.

Speaker 2: Okay, you're welcome.

Speaker 1: It's canceled, and you're all set.

Speaker 2: All right, thank you very much.

Speaker 1: You're welcome.

Speaker 2: Have a good day.
